@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Container widget for internal frames (iframes). An iframe can display any HTML page inside the widget. Example Here is a little example of how to use the widget. 

 var document = this.getRoot();
 var iframe = new qx.ui.embed.Iframe("http://www.qooxdoo.org");
 document.add(iframe);

External Documentation Documentation of this widget in the qooxdoo manual. Notes When modifying this file, note that the test qx.test.ui.embed.Iframe.testSyncSourceAfterDOMMove has been disabled under Chrome because of problems with Travis and Github. Changes to this file should be tested manually against that test.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: If the user presses F1 in IE by default the onhelp event is fired and IE’s help window is opened. Setting this property to false prevents this behavior. Note: This only works if the iframe source is served from the same domain as the main application.

@description.body: Checks if the iframe element is out of sync. This can happen in Firefox if the iframe is moved around and the source is changed right after. The root cause is that Firefox is reloading the iframe when its position in DOM has changed.
